The paper deals with optimization problems and learning from noisy point evaluations, which are common topics in machine learning and optimization. The use of Gaussian processes and online learning techniques further suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on trajectory planning for autonomous vehicles and the use of mixed strategies also suggest that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of game-theoretic concepts such as mixed strategies suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
